==English==
===Noun===
'''escutcheon'''
# {{heraldry}}: a tribal or family [[shield]] or [[coat of arms]]
# {{heraldry}}: a tribal or family [[crest]]
# the insignia around doorknob's exterior hardware or a door lock's cosmetic plate
# a flat protective covering (on a door or wall etc) to prevent soiling by user's fingers
===Derived terms===
"Blot on the escutcheon": A stain on the family name. (Probably from the little known and extremely turgid play of the same name by Robert Browning).